http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Body-found/article14026631.ece

The body of a tribal youth has been recovered from Gochhapada police station area of Kandhamal district in Odisha along with a handwritten letter in the name of Maoists.The body of the victim, identified as Biswamabar Kanhar in his thirties, was found near Kuaghar village near Balandapada police outpost and did not have any mark of injury by bullets or sharp weapons. Kanhar appeared to have died due to attack by some blunt thing. The letter in Odia found near the body claimed that Biswamabar had been killed as he was a police informer.